The issue is that when the opening brace `{` of the lambda is on a different line from where the function call starts, the alignment calculation doesn't make sense. 

The current code does:```kotlin
private fun ASTNode.calculateIndentOfFunctionLiteralParameters() =
    if (codeStyle == ktlint_official || isFirstParameterOfFunctionLiteralPrecededByNewLine()) {
        indentConfig.indent.repeat(2)
    } else {
        parent(CALL_EXPRESSION)
            ?.let { callExpression ->
                val textBeforeFirstParameter =                    callExpression.findChildByType(REFERENCE_EXPRESSION)?.text +
                        " { "
                " ".repeat(textBeforeFirstParameter.length)            }
            ?: indentConfig.indent.repeat(2)    }
```

The fix should be to add another condition: if the lambda brace is on a different line than the function call, use double indent.Let me check if I can detect whether the opening brace has a newline before it.

